data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but in EF Core 11 that opt-in is gone — all synchronous calls **always throw** at runtime, with no workaround.

Every method in your repository is affected:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();       // was ToList()
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id); // was First()
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();        // was Count()
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();                  // was SaveChanges()
    }
}
```

**Quick reference for the conversion:**

| Sync (throws in EF 11) | Async replacement |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |
| `Single()` / `Any()` | `await SingleAsync()` / `await AnyAsync()` |

You'll also need to propagate `async`/`await` up through all callers of these repository methods (controllers, services, etc.).
